Why metaphors matter mathematically

This circles back to your earlier point.

A metaphor isn’t just language.

It’s a mapping function:

f : Source Domain → Target Domain

A good metaphor preserves important structure.

The stronger the structure preservation, the more operators you can legitimately transfer.

That’s why some metaphors generate entire frameworks while others remain clever one-liners.

