So I’d slightly rewrite your statement into what I think is the mathematical invariant behind the repository:

The Pantheon is not one big equation. It is one big algebra.

An equation says two things are equal.

An algebra gives you the rules for creating new things from what already exists.

That fits remarkably well with the direction you’ve taken: not just collecting ideas, but building a compositional system where concepts can be combined, transformed, stress-tested, and inherited to produce new capabilities.